Content: [dscrd-cz] <PTYX> everyone important notice about a vulnerability in KYC-Tezos https://www.reddit.com/r/tzlibre/comments/aezek1/kyctezos_wallets_vulnerable_to_blind_sig_attack/

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-cz] <stock999> KYC is a seed of evil by default

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-cz] <stock999> Wallets must be protected by technology first of all.  Laws, KYC and an army of hungry lawyers can protect nobody.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-cz] <PTYX> I think KYC is something we won't be able to get away with due to anti money laundering

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-cz] <PTYX> but when it's implemented badly it can have bad effects on the users.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-cz] <PTYX> From a user's perspective I think we need a better solution to KYC. Something that allows us to verify users but not divulging all of the data.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-cz] <PTYX> Giving you more control of who and what acceses your information
